Students learn how to structure the process of teaching and learning foreign languages in contemporary school. Organizational formats of teaching and their application to the study of foreign languages. Students learn and apply various methods of teaching foreign languages, techniques and games to develop listening, speaking, reading, and writing skills. They learn to analyse various textbooks of German and work out their own conception of teaching German on the basis of one topic in the textbook. The course ends with an exam.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The students obtain and  analyse different  contemporary methods of teaching German languageLearning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The students learn to structure the process of teaching and work out their own conception of teaching
